{{Infobox military person |name=Ma Guoliang |birth_date= |death_date= |birth_place=[[Linxia County]], [[Gansu]] |death_place= |image= |caption= |nickname= |allegiance= [[File:Flag of the Qing Dynasty (1889-1912).svg|20px|Flag of the Qing dynasty]] [[Qing dynasty]] |serviceyears=1895 |rank= [[General officer|general]] |commands= |battles=[[Salar revolt]] |laterwork= }} {{Chinese name|[[Ma (surname)|Ma]]}}
'''Ma Guoliang''' ({{zh||s=马国良|t=馬國良|p=Mǎ Guóliáng|w=Ma Kuo-liang}}) was a [[Hui people|Hui]] Muslim military officer in the [[Qing dynasty]], the son of General [[Ma Zhanao]] and younger brother of General [[Ma Anliang]] and older brother of Ma Suiliang (Ma Sui-liang) 馬遂良.<ref>[http://nccur.lib.nccu.edu.tw/bitstream/140.119/33588/11/15301511.pdf 甘、寧、青三馬家族世系簡表]</ref> He helped crush a rebel Muslims in the [[Dungan revolt (1895–1896)]] along with his brother Ma Anliang, holding them off at Jishi pass.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=90CN0vtxdY0C&pg=PA191&lpg=PA191&dq=ma+anliang&source=bl&ots=gMwMFtA3op&sig=w_PGN0cI0LeR80GUe0wDXNe6tC4&hl=en&ei=rUohTIz0CMLflgeV7rlH&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4&ved=0CCAQ6AEwAw#v=snippet&q=ma%20guoliang%20jishi%20pass&f=false|title=Familiar strangers: a history of Muslims in Northwest China|author=Jonathan Neaman Lipman|year=2004|publisher=University of Washington Press|location=Seattle|page=155|isbn=0-295-97644-6|accessdate=2010-06-28}}</ref> His sons were Ma Tingbin (Ma T'ing-pin) 馬廷斌 aka Ma Quanqin [[w:zh:馬全欽|馬全欽]], and Ma Jieqin [[w:zh:馬介欽|馬介欽]].
In 1917 Ma Anliang ordered Ma Guoliang to suppress a rebellion of Tibetans in [[Xunhua]] who rebelled because of taxes Ma Anliang imposed on them. Ma Anliang did not report it to the central government in Beijing and was reprimanded for it, and [[Ma Qi]] was sent by the government to investigate the case and suppress the rebellion.<ref name=zsy>赵颂尧，马安良其人与民初的甘肃政争，西北民族大学学报(哲学社会科学版) 1989年第02期</ref>
Ma Guoliang's son Ma Quanqin later defected to the Communists in 1949 and became a member of the Communist party.
