'''William Fernandez''' was a [[Luso-Africans|Luso-African]] in the [[Pongo River (Guinea)|Pongo River]] area of [[Guinea]] in the early nineteenth century.
In the 1750s [[William Settel Fernandez]] married the daughtrer of a [[Baga people|Baga]] leader.<ref name=Brooks>{{cite book|last1=Brooks|first1=George E.|title=Eurafricans in western Africa : commerce, social status, gender and religious observance from the sixteenth to eighteenth century|date=2003|publisher=James Currey|location=Oxford|isbn=978-0852554890|edition=1. publ.}}</ref> ==References== {{reflist}}
